Use of cookies by Newegg

A cookie is a small text file that is generated by a website and is stored on your device. When you access our site, a number of cookies used by Newegg and third parties are sent to your browser and stored on your device. When you next visit our site, Newegg and the third parties will use this information to recognize and remember your device. We use cookies and similar technologies to make our site work and to improve our site and our services. You can manage cookies though your browser’s settings. Please note that some of the uses of the site and the services provided on the site may not function if cookies are disabled. Further information about the cookies and similar technologies we use on the site can be found in our privacy policy. Privacy Policy

Strictly Necessary Cookies

.

These cookies are essential in order to enable you to move around the site and use its features and cannot be turned off. Without these cookies, services you have asked for (such as navigating between pages, placing an order and using a shopping cart or e-billing services) cannot be provided. Therefore, you cannot disable these cookies.

Functional Cookies

.

These cookies are used to provide you with certain functionality on the site. For example, to improve the performance of our services and the site, to maintain security on the site and to prevent and detect fraud, to customise your account, to display certain web page content based upon your browser type and other device information.

Performance Cookies

.

These cookies allow us to analyse how our visitors use the site and monitor the site’s performance. This allows us to provide a high quality experience by customising our offering, and quickly identifying and fixing any issues that arise. The information collected by these cookies is not associated with your personal data by us or by our contractors.

Advertising Cookies

.

Newegg and various third party ad partners may use these cookies to tailor advertising to your interests through tracking your browsing across websites.
